{
  "local_port": 41330,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I want to change my name in my class 10 CBSE certificate, but I'm currently living in KSA and I'm not an Indian. What should I do?",
  "response": "If you\u2019re not an Indian and wish to change your name on your Class 10 CBSE certificate while living in KSA, the process can be a bit complex but manageable. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Check CBSE Guidelines**\n   - Visit the official CBSE website (https://www.cbse.gov.in) to review their guidelines for name correction/change in certificates.\n   - Look for the specific rules that apply to foreign nationals or students residing abroad.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Gather Required Documents**\n   Prepare the necessary documents for the name change, which typically include:\n   - Original Class 10 CBSE mark sheet and certificate.\n   - Proof of the new name (e.g., passport, government-issued ID, or legal name change document).\n   - Affidavit for name change (signed and notarized).\n   - Gazette notification (if required, especially for legal name changes in your country of residence).\n   - Application form (available on the CBSE website or from the school).\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Affidavit and Gazette Notification**\n   - Obtain an affidavit for the name change from a legal authority in KSA.\n   - If required by CBSE, get your name change published in the official gazette of your country (this may not always be necessary for CBSE, but confirm the requirement).\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Contact Your School**\n   - Reach out to the school where you appeared for the Class 10 CBSE exams.\n   - Submit the application form and supporting documents to the school for verification and endorsement.\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Submit Application to CBSE**\n   - Once the school has verified your documents, they will forward your application to the CBSE regional office.\n   - If the school is unable to assist, contact the CBSE regional office directly for guidance.\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Consulate/Embassy Assistance**\n   - If you face difficulties in communication or document submission, you can seek assistance from the Indian Embassy/Consulate in KSA. They can guide you on the process and help with document verification.\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Pay Applicable Fees**\n   - CBSE charges a fee for name correction/change. Confirm the fee structure and payment method (online or via demand draft).\n\n---\n\n### 8. **Follow Up**\n   - Keep track of the application status through the CBSE website or your school.\n   - The process may take several months, so be patient.\n\n---\n\n### Important Notes:\n   - Ensure all documents are accurate and match the requirements listed by CBSE.\n   - If your passport already reflects the new name, it can serve as strong evidence for the name change.\n   - Always communicate with CBSE or your school via email for written records of your queries and submissions.\n\n---\n\nFor further assistance, contact the CBSE helpline or visit their official website. If you\u2019re unsure about any step, consult an education consultant or legal advisor familiar with CBSE procedures.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
